---
/**
 * rest-api · 0006-pagination-at-scale · Figure 3 — "PAGE DRIFT · ONE INSERT
 * POISONS EVERY OFFSET" (a head insert shifts every offset, so row E is shown
 * twice across the page boundary).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0006-pagination-at-scale.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Component, not inline, because MDX's JSX parser
 * mishandles kebab-case SVG attributes. References the red arrow marker
 * (url(#arwR)); the source declared it in a shared body <defs>, so it's embedded
 * locally here to keep the SVG self-contained.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 220"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A new row inserted at the head shifts every offset down by one, so row E is shown twice across the page boundary and a row is skipped"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path>
            </marker>
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">PAGE DRIFT · ONE INSERT POISONS EVERY OFFSET</text
            >

            <text
                x="150"
                y="42"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">① fetch page 1 (OFFSET 0)</text
            >
            <rect x="92" y="50" width="116" height="22" rx="3" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect><text x="150" y="65" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10">A</text>
            <rect x="92" y="74" width="116" height="22" rx="3" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect><text x="150" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10">B</text>
            <rect x="92" y="98" width="116" height="22" rx="3" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect><text x="150" y="113" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10">C</text>
            <rect x="92" y="122" width="116" height="22" rx="3" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect><text x="150" y="137" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10">D</text>
            <rect
                x="92"
                y="146"
                width="116"
                height="22"
                rx="3"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect><text
                x="150"
                y="161"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">E ← last on page 1</text
            >

            <text
                x="320"
                y="92"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">② row Z inserted</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >at the head, before</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="120" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >page 2 is fetched</text
            >
            <line
                x1="216"
                y1="135"
                x2="424"
                y2="135"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-dasharray="4 3"
                marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
            <text x="320" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >every offset shifts down by 1</text
            >

            <text
                x="490"
                y="42"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">③ fetch page 2 (OFFSET 5)</text
            >
            <rect x="432" y="50" width="116" height="22" rx="3" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect><text
                x="490"
                y="65"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">Z (new, row 0)</text
            >
            <rect x="432" y="74" width="116" height="22" rx="3" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect><text x="490" y="89" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >A B C D pushed down</text
            >
            <rect
                x="432"
                y="98"
                width="116"
                height="22"
                rx="3"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect><text
                x="490"
                y="113"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">E shown AGAIN 💥</text
            >
            <text x="490" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >E is a duplicate;</text
            >
            <text x="490" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >had Z been a delete, a</text
            >
            <text x="490" y="162" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >row would be skipped</text
            >

            <text x="320" y="205" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#7a1f12"
                >The offset points at a <tspan font-style="italic">position</tspan>, and positions
                move when the data moves.</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Insert at the head → duplicate across the boundary. Delete at the head → a skipped row. The
        bug scales with write rate, so it's invisible in a quiet dev DB.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
